<font color="#FF0000">ATTN:VIETNAM VETS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jun  3 20:18:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This is for onyxman;  I'm a grunt from 1968.  Didn't do anything to anybody but got drafted. I learned my craft and spent a year of my life in Vietnam, doing what a soldier does.  I didn't sleep in a bed for a year, and could count the hot showers on my two hands.  The meals were as sparce.  I came home in November, got married five days later, and I'm still married to my wonderful, caring, patriotic, wife.  She was always there, not like other &quot;patriots&quot; of the sixties.  I have had only two jobs, one for ten years, the other I'm still at. Never been arrested for anything, never missed an election, and coached Y&gt;M&gt;C&gt;A&gt; softball for eight years.  I think I 've had nothing to get over except attitudes that mark me as different, because I obeyed when my Country called for me.  If we have a difficult decision to make,as a country, I'm hoping there are others like I was, instead of a yellow, insecure, offensive nothing of value, indiviual.  I asked for nothing, took nothing, and now I won't take your vile.
<p><code>-- kfoulkes@epix.net  (Ken Foulkes) </code><p>


